Package com.ibm.cloud.objectstorage.config.resource_configuration.v1.model

Class ActivityTracking

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ibm.cloud.sdk.core.service.model.GenericModel
      • com.ibm.cloud.objectstorage.config.resource_configuration.v1.model.ActivityTracking
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.ibm.cloud.sdk.core.service.model.ObjectModel
    public class ActivityTracking
extends com.ibm.cloud.sdk.core.service.model.GenericModel
    Enables sending log data to Activity Tracker and LogDNA to provide visibility into object read and write events. All object events are sent to the activity tracker instance defined in the `activity_tracker_crn` field.

        public Boolean isReadDataEvents()

      • isWriteDataEvents

        public Boolean isWriteDataEvents()

        Returns:
        the writeDataEvents

      • getActivityTrackerCrn

        public String getActivityTrackerCrn()
        Gets the activityTrackerCrn. Required the first time `activity_tracking` is configured. The instance of Activity Tracker that will recieve object event data. The format is "crn:v1:bluemix:public:logdnaat:{bucket location}:a/{storage account}:{activity tracker service instance}::".
        Returns:
        the activityTrackerCrn
